n    <p>To replace all existing classes with another class, we can use <code>.attr( &quot;class&quot;, &quot;newClass&quot; )</code> instead.</p>\n    <p>As of jQuery 1.4, the <code>.removeClass()</code> method allows us to indicate the class to be removed by passing in a function.</p>\n    <div class=\"syntaxhighlighter javascript\">\n	<table>\n		<tbody>\n			<tr>\n				\n				<td class=\"gutter\">\n					\n						<div class=\"line n1\">1</div>\n					\n						<div class=\"line n2\">2</div>\n					\n						<div class=\"line n3\">3</div>\n					\n				</td>\n				\n				<td class=\"code\">\n					<pre><div class=\"container\"><div class=\"line\"><code>$( <span class=\"string\">&quot;li:last&quot;</span> ).removeClass(<span class=\"keyword\">function</span>() {</code></div></div><div class=\"container\"><div class=\"line\"><code>  <span class=\"keyword\">return</span> $( <span class=\"keyword\">this</span> ).prev().attr( <span class=\"string\">&quot;class&quot;</span> );</code></div></div><div class=\"container\"><div class=\"line\"><code>});</code></div></div></pre>\n				</td>\n			</tr>\n		</tbody>\n	</table>\n</div>\n\n    <p>This example removes the class name of the penultimate <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> from the last <code>&lt;li&gt;</code>.</p>\n  ','[\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<pre><div class=\\\"container\\\"><div class=\\\"line\\\"><code><span class=\\\"doctype\\\">&lt;!doctype html&gt;</span></code></div></div><div class=\\\"container\\\"><div class=\\\"line\\\"><code><span class=\\\"tag\\\">&lt;<span class=\\\"title\\\">html</span> <span class=\\\"attribute\\\">lang</span>=<span class=\\\"value\\\">&quot;en&quot;</span>&gt;</span></code></div></div><div class=\\\"container\\\"><div class=\\\"line\\\"><code><span class=\\\"tag\\\">&lt;<span class=\\\"title\\\">head</span>&gt;</span></code></div></div><div class=\\\"container\\\"><div class=\\\"line\\\"><code>  <span class=\\\"tag\\\">&lt;<span class=\\\"title\\\">meta</span> <span class=\\\"attribute\\\">charset</span>=<span class